## Code Example

```python
# Example: skeleton DoFn using Firestore policy to validate records
class ValidateWithPolicy(DoFn):
    def setup(self):
        self.firestore_client = firestore.Client()
        self.policy_cache = {}

    def process(self, element):
        # Load policy from Firestore with caching
        policy = self.get_policy(element.get('schema_version'))

        # Validate fields/types against policy
        if self.validate_record(element, policy):
            yield element
        else:
            # Send invalid records to dead-letter sink
            yield pvalue.TaggedOutput('invalid', {
                'record': element,
                'metadata': {
                    'timestamp': datetime.utcnow().isoformat(),
                    'validation_errors': self.get_validation_errors(element, policy)
                }
            })
```

